results.name: Triangle T(n,k) giving number of labeled cyclic subgroups of order k in symmetric group S_n, n >= 1, 1 <= k <= g(n), where g(n) = A000793(n) is Landau's function.
comment: A057731 contains zeros.  This sequence contains only positive values of A057731(n,k)/A000010(k). - _Alois P. Heinz_, Feb 16 2013
link: Alois P. Heinz, Rows n = 1..42, flattened
mathematica: T[n_, k_] := n! SeriesCoefficient[O[x]^(n+1) + Sum[MoebiusMu[k/i]*Exp[ Sum[x^j/j, {j, Divisors[i]}]], {i, Divisors[k]}], {x, 0, n}]/ EulerPhi[k];
Table[DeleteCases[Table[T[n, k], {k, 1, 2 nmax}], 0], {n, 1, nmax}] // Flatten (* _Jean-François Alcover_, Sep 16 2019, after _Andrew Howroyd_ *)
program: (PARI) T(n,k)={n!*polcoeff(sumdiv(k, i, moebius(k/i)*exp(sumdiv(i, j, x^j/j) + O(x*x^n))), n)/eulerphi(k)} \\ _Andrew Howroyd_, Jul 02 2018
